        "body": "Fixes #88024\n\nNote: this pull request was made with AI assistance.\n\n## Summary\n- Initialize the Feishu plugin runtime when the gateway starts the Feishu monitor with a plugin runtime.\n- Add startup regression coverage that verifies monitor startup stores the runtime before account monitors run.\n\n## Verification\n- `docker run --rm -v /tmp/openclaw-work.DNxJRE/repo:/workspace -w /workspace node:24-bookworm bash -lc 'corepack enable && node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/feishu/src/monitor.startup.test.ts'` (6 tests passed)\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Feishu WebSocket monitor startup now stores the gateway plugin runtime before account monitor dispatch, so inbound handlers using `getFeishuRuntime()` do not see an uninitialized runtime.\nReal environment tested: Containerized OpenClaw checkout using `node:24-bookworm` with workspace dependencies installed; no live Feishu credentials.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `docker run --rm -v /tmp/openclaw-work.DNxJRE/repo:/workspace -w /workspace node:24-bookworm bash -lc 'corepack enable && node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/feishu/src/monitor.startup.test.ts'`\nEvidence after fix: `extension-feishu ../../extensions/feishu/src/monitor.startup.test.ts` reported 1 test file passed and 6 tests passed; the new regression assertion observes `setFeishuRuntime(runtime)` during monitor startup.\nObserved result after fix: Feishu monitor startup initializes the plugin runtime before account monitors are allowed to start.\nWhat was not tested: Live Feishu WebSocket delivery with real Feishu app credentials.\n",
